
Overview of noun revere

The noun revere has 2 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                       
1. Revere, Paul Revere -- (American silversmith remembered for his midnight ride (celebrated in a poem by Longfellow) to warn the colonists in Lexington and Concord that British troops were coming (1735-1818))
2. revers, revere -- (a lapel on a woman's garment; turned back to show the reverse side)

Overview of verb revere

The verb revere has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (2) idolize, idolise, worship, hero-worship, revere -- (love unquestioningly and uncritically or to excess; venerate as an idol; "Many teenagers idolized the Beatles")
2. (1) reverence, fear, revere, venerate -- (regard with feelings of respect and reverence; consider hallowed or exalted or be in awe of; "Fear God as your father"; "We venerate genius")
